    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="892"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d892">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A Pacific War/823: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-19">November 19,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received November 29—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–492. American interest Japan. Civilian internment camps, Legation’s airgram
                    402, October 18. Foreign Office note November 16 states Swiss Legation Tokyo
                    forwarded following information in reply similarly numbered paragraphs
                    Department’s airgram 259, July 20.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>Men of Confidence stated conversion rate fixed by Japanese authorities.
                        Internees not required make purchases, able retain dollars without
                        requesting conversion.</item>
                    <label>(3)</label>
                    <item>Internees authorized forward monthly English letter 100 words or two
                        letters weekly 500 words Japanese.</item>
                    <pb facs="1021" n="1009" xml:id="pg_1009"/>
                    <label>(4)</label>
                    <item>In principle witnesses present interviews but majority cases do not follow
                        conversation.</item>
                    <label>(5)</label>
                    <item>Absence canteen due difficulty obtain merchandise. Furthermore, local
                        authorities have ordered Kobe merchants visits camps periodically.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
